  "prompt": "I am an average student preparing for the IIT-JEE. Which test series is the best for me for free?",
  "response": "Preparing for the IIT-JEE demands rigorous practice and assessment. While there are several paid test series available, as an average student looking for free options, you can explore the following:\n\n1. **NTA Abhyas App:** This app is provided by the National Testing Agency and offers a wide range of free mock tests specifically designed for JEE Main and NEET aspirants.\n\n2. **Khan Academy:** While not a test series, Khan Academy offers free resources and practice problems that align with the JEE syllabus, which can be very beneficial.\n\n3. **Toppr:** Toppr sometimes offers free tests and resources. It's worth checking their app or website for any free test series or materials.\n\n4. **Vedantu:** Vedantu often conducts free live classes, webinars, and mock tests. Keep an eye on their website for free resources related to the JEE examination.\n\n5. **Embibe:** This platform offers a few free tests and personalized learning experiences. You can try some of their free offerings to see if they match your preparation needs.\n\n6. **YouTube Channels and Educators:** Many educators on YouTube offer free JEE Main and Advanced series. Channels like Unacademy JEE, Physics Wallah, and others can be useful for free tests and preparation tips.\n\n7. **EduRev:** This platform provides a variety of free content including tests and preparation material for JEE aspirants.\n\n8. **Mission JEE Website and Telegram Groups:** There are numerous Telegram groups specifically dedicated to JEE preparation that share free test series and study materials.\n\nRemember, while practicing with these test resources, consistent evaluation and understanding where you need improvement are key to excelling in JEE. Additionally, don\u2019t hesitate to combine these free tests with other free resources like online study materials, video lectures, and question banks to optimize your preparation.",
